Label: Vessel
Name: Vessel (hypointensities in left basal ganglia)
Name_spanish: Vasos sanguíneos (hipointensidades en ganglios basales izquierdos)

Label: Vessel
Name: Vessel (hypointensities in right basal ganglia)
Name_spanish: Vasos sanguíneos (hipointensidades en ganglios basales derechos)

Label: WM-hypointensities
Name: White matter hypointensities
Description: Dark white matter on a T1-weighted image

Label: non-WM-hypointensities
Name: Gray matter hypointensities
Description: Dark gray matter on a T1-weighted image

Label: CC_Posterior
Name: Corpus callosum: posterior division
Description: The divisions of the cc are equally spaced in terms of distance along the primary eigendirection (pretty much the long axis) of the cc.

Label: CC_Mid_Posterior
Name: Corpus callosum: middle posterior division
Description: The divisions of the cc are equally spaced in terms of distance along the primary eigendirection (pretty much the long axis) of the cc.

Label: CC_Central
Name: Corpus callosum: central division
Description: The divisions of the cc are equally spaced in terms of distance along the primary eigendirection (pretty much the long axis) of the cc.

Label: CC_Mid_Anterior
Name: Corpus callosum: middle anterior division
Description: The divisions of the cc are equally spaced in terms of distance along the primary eigendirection (pretty much the long axis) of the cc.

Label: CC_Anterior
Name: Corpus callosum: anterior division
Description: The divisions of the cc are equally spaced in terms of distance along the primary eigendirection (pretty much the long axis) of the cc.

Label: BrainSegVol
Name: Cerebral hemispheres, diencephalum, cerebellum, and cerebrospinal fluid
Name_spanish: Hemisferios cerebrales, diencéfalo, cerebelo y líquido cefalorraquídeo
Description: volume of all voxels in the aparc+aseg.mgz that are neither background nor brain stem. This is the same as pre-5.2 versions except that brain stem is not included. This will also include the "vessel", "optic-chiasm", and "CSF" segmentations. This is just a simple count of voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz. There are also additional stats for voxel-based supratentorial volume and surface based brain seg volume.

Label: BrainSegVolNotVent
Name: Cerebral hemispheres, diencephalum, and cerebellum
Description: same as BrainSeg without ventricles (lateral, inferior lateral, 3rd, 4th, 5th), CSF, and choroid plexus

Label: BrainSegVolNotVentSurf
Name: Cerebral hemispheres, diencephalum, and cerebellum (surface-based)
Name_spanish: Hemisferios cerebrales, diencéfalo y cerebelo (basado en la superficie)
Description: There are also additional stats for voxel-based supratentorial volume and surface based brain seg volume.

Label: lhCortexVol
Name: Cortex: left hemisphere
Description: volume inside the pial surface minus the volume inside the white surface minus tissue inside the ribbon that is not part of cortex (eg, hippocampus). This uses the surface-based volume calculation and is not a voxel count. It is approximately equal to the count of cortical label voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: rhCortexVol
Name: Cortex: right hemisphere
Description: volume inside the pial surface minus the volume inside the white surface minus tissue inside the ribbon that is not part of cortex (eg, hippocampus). This uses the surface-based volume calculation and is not a voxel count. It is approximately equal to the count of cortical label voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: CortexVol
Name: Cortex: both hemispheres
Description: volume inside the pial surface minus the volume inside the white surface minus tissue inside the ribbon that is not part of cortex (eg, hippocampus). This uses the surface-based volume calculation and is not a voxel count. It is approximately equal to the count of cortical label voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: lhCerebralWhiteMatterVol
Name: White matter: left hemisphere
Description: volume inside the white surface minus anything that is not WM. CerebralWhiteMatter includes hypointensities. Does not include cerebellar white matter or brainstem. This uses the surface-based volume computation for part of the calculation and counts voxels to subtract "anything not in WM". It is approximately equal to the count of WM voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: rhCerebralWhiteMatterVol
Name: White matter: right hemisphere
Description: volume inside the white surface minus anything that is not WM. CerebralWhiteMatter includes hypointensities. Does not include cerebellar white matter or brainstem. This uses the surface-based volume computation for part of the calculation and counts voxels to subtract "anything not in WM". It is approximately equal to the count of WM voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: CerebralWhiteMatterVol
Name: White matter: both hemispheres
Description: volume inside the white surface minus anything that is not WM. CerebralWhiteMatter includes hypointensities. Does not include cerebellar white matter or brainstem. This uses the surface-based volume computation for part of the calculation and counts voxels to subtract "anything not in WM". It is approximately equal to the count of WM voxels in aparc+aseg.mgz

Label: SubCortGrayVol
Name: Basal ganglia, diencephalum and subtantia nigra
Name_spanish: Ganglios basales, diencéfalo y sustancia negra
Description: includes thalamus, caudate, putamen, pallidum, hippocampus, amygdala, accumbens, ventral DC, substancia nigra (if there). This is a simple voxel count of structures identified as subcortical GM. The function used to define this is IsSubCorticalGray() in cma.c. NOTE: SubCortGray excludes brain stem and cerebellum with 5.2.

Label: TotalGrayVol
Name: Cortical, subcortical and cerebellar gray matter
Name_spanish: Sustancia gris cortical, subcortical y cerebelar
Description: total gray matter volume. This is simply the sum of lhCortex + rhCortex + SubCortGray + CerebellumGM. As such, it includes both surface-based volume calculations and voxel counts.

Label: SupraTentorialVol
Name: Supratentorial cerebrospinal fluid and structures
Description: includes everything except cerebellum (GM and WM) and brain stem. It is computed based on everything inside the pial surface plus any structures that might fall partially or totally outside of the pial, e.g., hippocampus, amygdala, corpus callosum, ventral DC, thalamus, ventricles, and choroid plexus. The function that determines the volume of structures outside of the supratentorium is SupraTentorialVolCorrection() in cma.c. Note that SupraTentorial includes ventricle, choroid plexus, and vessel. This uses surface-based volume calculations and voxel counts

Label: SupraTentorialVolNotVent
Name: Supratentorial structures
Description: same as SupraTentorial but subracting the volume ventricles (lateral,inferior lateral, 3rd, 4th, 5th), CSF, and choroid plexus.

Label: MaskVol
Name: Brain mask
Description: count of non-zero voxels in the brainmask.mgz. In general, this is not useful for reporting results but might be handy for QA.

Label: BrainSegVol-to-eTIV
Name: Ratio of cerebral hemispheres, diencephalum, cerebellum, and cerebrospinal fluid to intracraneal volume
Name_spanish: Razón de volumen de hemisferios cerebrales, diencéfalo, cerebelo y líquido cefalorraquídeo a volumen intracraneal

Label: MaskVol-to-eTIV
Name: Ratio of brain mask to intracranial volume
Name_spanish: Razón de volumen de la máscara del encéfalo a volumen intracraneal

Label: lhSurfaceHoles
Name: Number of holes in the reconstructed surface of the left hemisphere prior to fixing
Name_spanish: Número de hoyos en la superficie reconstruida del hemisferio izquierdo antes de reparar
Description: Number of defect holes in lh surfaces prior to fixing

Label: rhSurfaceHoles
Name: Number of holes in the reconstructed surface of the right hemisphere prior to fixing
Name_spanish: Número de hoyos en la superficie reconstruida del hemisferio derecho antes de reparar
Description: Number of defect holes in rh surfaces prior to fixing

Label: SurfaceHoles
Name: Number of holes in the reconstructed surfaces of both hemisphere prior to fixing
Name_spanish: Número de hoyos en la superficie reconstruida de ambos hemisferios antes de reparar
Description: Total number of defect holes in surfaces prior to fixing

Label: EstimatedTotalIntraCranialVol
Name: Intracranial volume
Description: This is the same number as the IntraCrainialVol (ICV) from pre-5.2 verions. The name was changed to help avoid confusion as to what this number is and is not. It is NOT is a count of voxels inside the skull. The eTIV is a metric computed from the amount of scaling in the talairach.xfm file. See http://surfer.nmr.mgh.harvard.edu/fswiki/eTIV
